FBIS4-23939 "drafr118_d_94013" FBIS-AFR-94-118 Daily Report 18 Jun 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Angola Issues Statement on Aid Flights Issues Statement on Aid Flights MB1806152594 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in Portuguese 1200 GMT 18 Jun 94 MB1806152594 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro Portuguese BFN [Communique issued by the Chief of General Staff of FALA in Huambo; date not given] [Text] 1. The General Staff of the Armed Forces for the Liberation of Angola [FALA] would like to vehemently deny that it is responsible for the suspension of humanitarian aid flights, as pointed out by Mrs. Mercedes Sayagues, World Food Program [WFP] representative for southern Africa. Humanitarian aid flights were canceled by the Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola-Labor Party [MPLA-PT] government with the WFP's deliberate complicity. 2. The FALA General Staff would like to clarify that Huambo remains open for any humanitarian assistance. This assistance can be sent by air or by land as is most convenient for the involved organizations. 3. The FALA General Staff does not understand and does not want to understand that humanitarian assistance [words indistinct]. 4. The FALA General Staff would like to guarantee in its areas the freedom of flights and land movement [words indistinct]. 5. UNITA [words indistinct] to recolonize our country [words indistinct] the MPLA-PT government, particularly children and women [words indistinct]. 6. UNITA's reaction [words indistinct] the special representative of the UN secretary general [words indistinct]. [Issued] [Words indistinct] June 1994 [Signed] Army General Arlindo Chenda Isaac Pena Ben-Ben, FALA chief of the General Staff.
